sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K611067
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct is used for testing the promoter activity in the barcode region of the cI Lambda biobrick, (BBa_C0051). The first 110 bases have been truncated in order to rule out the possibility that leaky expression of the protein was affecting the transcription of the downstream RFP (BBa_E1010).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Timothy Fenton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Plasmid for construction of promoter basic parts. Insertion of a promoter element between XbaI and SpeI sites results in a RFP reporter while retaining the ability to do biobrick assembly. Part J61002 is the tet promoter variant of the plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K611090
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a truncated version of BBa_C0051. The first 110 bases were truncated leaving a 640 base pair, non-functional coding region. This was designed to rule out any protein interaction with the promoter activity of the barcode region of BBa_C0051.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Timothy Fenton
